Eastern Platinum (Eastplats) reports that during December 2020 its subsidiary, Barplats Mines, delivered its first shipment of pressed filter cake platinum group metals concentrate under the existing offtake agreement between Barplats and Impala Refining Services, now Impala Platinum. During 2020, the company completed the refurbishment of the small-scale PGM circuit. Eastplats only restarted and began operating the PGM Circuit D during Q3, 2020. Read more about mining for platinum The company has generated approximately 134 tons of pressed filter cake PGM concentrate and delivered approximately 32.18 tons during 2020 under the Offtake Agreement. Eastplats forecasts continued ramping up of the PGM Circuit D production and additional revenue from it during 2021. Read more about mining in South Africa Barplats’ tailings retreatment project located at its Crocodile River Mine has been recovering chrome since December 2018. With the refurbishment and operation of the PGM Circuit D, and utilizing the retreatment project source material, the company is now able to generate PGM revenue. Listen: Deep Insights #26: State of the SA mining industry Diana Hu, the President and CEO of Eastplats, states: “Operating the PGM Circuit D allows us to diversify its revenue sources and is a direct benefit of the retreatment project. “To build on this success, Eastplats intends to use part of the expected proceeds from the currently ongoing rights offering to further upgrade the PGM Circuit D and refurbish the existing main PGM facility thereby expanding its PGM processing capacity and potential revenue sources. “We are pleased to continue the development of opportunities in South Africa for its shareholders.”